        <h3 class="cag-h3">How Do You Spot a Timneh Scam Seller?</h3>
        <p>Our <a href="/how-to-avoid-african-grey-parrot-scams/">African Grey scam-prevention guide</a> lays out the whole pattern, but the shape is quick to learn: a keyword-stuffed domain, photos lifted from real breeders, an address that leads nowhere, and a price no genuine bird could carry. Once you've spotted it, you'll notice it playing out in the very results this page shares.</p>

        <h4 class="cag-h4">Which Payment or Shipping Red Flags Mean You Should Walk?</h4>
        <p>Scammers trip over two things almost without fail — the way they ask to be paid and the way they claim to ship — so wire both up as alarms. The instant a payment method can't be clawed back or a delivery promise breaks the law, no adorable photo or hard-luck story should keep you at the table.</p>

        <h5 class="cag-h5">Gift Cards, "24-Hour International Shipping" and $750 Bait Prices Are Scam Signals</h5>
        <p>A seller who insists on gift cards or cash apps has picked payment rails you can never reverse — reason enough to walk. And when a first-page Timneh listing brags about "24-hour international shipping to Canada and Australia," it is promising something CITES flatly forbids for an Appendix-I parrot, so read it as a blaring alarm, not a perk.</p>

        <h6 class="cag-h6">A Page-1 Timneh Result Right Now Cloaks Real Visitors to a Bot Wall</h6>
        <p>This isn't point-scoring: one of the highest-ranking pages for "timneh african grey for sale" quietly bounces real visitors into a bot-check loop instead of ever showing a parrot, while another advertises the illegal overseas shipping described just above. We wrote this whole section because those very sites share the results page with us.</p>

        <h3 class="cag-h3">Can You Verify C.A.Gs Before You Pay? Yes — in About 60 Seconds</h3>
        <p>The fastest cure for scam nerves is a task you can finish in about sixty seconds — prove to yourself that we're real. Work through the four checks below: since we're a licensed aviary at a genuine Texas address with a named pair standing behind Elad and Evie, every check comes back clean, which is precisely the test a phantom farm can't pass.</p>

