        <h4 class="cag-h4">What Proof Do You Get Before Any Money Moves?</h4>
        <p>Ahead of any deposit, we hand over what a con artist simply cannot: our license particulars, a live video of the actual bird, and a written rundown of the documents that will travel with it. Proof belongs before the payment, not as a promise made afterward — that ordering is the entire idea.</p>

        <h5 class="cag-h5">A Lookup-Able USDA Number, CITES Papers, Our Midland-TX Address and a Video Call With Your Bird</h5>
        <p>None of our proof is vague: a USDA license you can look up on <a href="https://www.aphis.usda.gov/aphis/ourfocus/animalwelfare" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the USDA APHIS public search</a>, CITES Appendix I captive-bred records, a real Midland, TX address printed on our <a href="/contact-us/">contact page</a>, and a live video with the very Timneh you're weighing up. Line those four up and we stop resembling any of the listings crowded around us.</p>

