        <p>That range looks wild until you realize the price tag isn't really on the bird — it's on everything standing behind it: the age, the months of hand-feeding, the lab and vet work, the temperament and the paper trail. A weaned, documented Timneh settles into the believable middle around $1,500 to $2,600, marked-up classified listings drift toward $6,500, and the bargain basement below the floor is where the fraud hides.</p>

