        <p>When a Timneh is dangled at $750 under a ticking "limited-time" clock, the number itself is the tell: no one can hand-feed, DNA-test, vet-check and document a grey for that and stay in business. <a href="/how-to-avoid-african-grey-parrot-scams/">Our breakdown of parrot fraud</a> shows why the urgency is deliberate — it exists to hurry you past that math before you run it yourself.</p>

        <h5 class="cag-h5">Hand-Rearing, DNA and Disease Testing, Age and Paperwork Set the Real Price</h5>
