        <h4 class="cag-h4">Can You Collect a Timneh in Person Rather Than Ship?</h4>
        <p>Absolutely — collecting your Timneh at our Midland, TX aviary is the softest possible handoff, and it's open to anyone who can make the 2–3 hour drive. Coming in person also lets you run, face to face, the very verification this whole page has been walking you through.</p>
        <img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/african-grey-nationwide-shipping-7-metro-map.webp" width="1408" height="768" loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="Map of nationwide African Grey shipping routes from Midland, Texas to major US metros" />

        <h5 class="cag-h5">Airport Cargo Runs $185 and Door Delivery $350 on Delta, United or American</h5>
        <p>One more time, plainly: $185 for the airport, $350 for your door, every flight US-only on IATA-approved carriers — Delta, United or American. Those lanes reach most of the places our Timnehs land, and each card below opens that region's availability page:</p>
        <div class="geo-cards">
